@namespace PgmStudio.Client.Pages.AuthoringParts

<section class="ds-section" id="focus">
  <div class="ds-section-heading">
    <div>
      <p class="ds-kicker">08</p>
      <h2>Side-view &amp; per-side focus</h2>
    </div>
    <p>The plan canvas is top-down, so a drawn point has no obvious Y, and a whole-map zoom fights small
       edits. Two controls solve both.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="ds-example-grid">
    <article class="ds-example">
      <div class="ds-example-label">Side-view slice (inspector) — set Y on a flat map</div>
      <div class="ds-panel-frame">
        <div class="workspace-scroll">
          <section class="panel-section">
            <div class="detail-header">
              <span class="geo-type-icon detail-icon--muted"><i data-lucide="dot"></i></span>
              <span class="detail-label detail-label--mono">wool-spawn</span>
              <span class="badge badge--neutral">Point</span>
            </div>
            <div class="section-body">
              <div class="field">
                <div class="slice-head">
                  <label class="field-label">Side view — drag the line to set Y</label>
                  <div class="slice-axis">
                    <button class="draw-tool-btn draw-tool-btn--active" title="Inspect from −Z">Z−</button>
                    <button class="draw-tool-btn" title="Inspect from +Z">Z+</button>
                    <button class="draw-tool-btn" title="Inspect from −X">X−</button>
                    <button class="draw-tool-btn" title="Inspect from +X">X+</button>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="slice-view" style="position:relative">
                  <canvas class="slice-canvas"></canvas>
                  <span style="position:absolute;left:0;right:0;top:44%;height:2px;background:var(--accent);opacity:.85;pointer-events:none"></span>
                  <span style="position:absolute;right:6px;top:33%;font-size:10px;color:var(--accent);font-family:ui-monospace,monospace;pointer-events:none">Y 10</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <p class="section-desc">Point / block → a draggable Y line seats it on the terrain surface (persisted as a
                 coords patch). Rectangle → the slice is display-only (read the profile under a wool room). Four inspect
                 directions read the near face from whichever side is unobstructed.</p>
            </div>
          </section>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="ds-example">
      <div class="ds-example-label">Per-side focus (canvas subbar) — frame one quadrant</div>
      <div class="ds-canvas-bar-example canvas-subbar">
        <div class="canvas-toolbar">
          <button class="draw-tool-btn draw-tool-btn--active" title="Pan"><i data-lucide="hand"></i></button>
          <button class="draw-tool-btn" title="Select"><i data-lucide="mouse-pointer-2"></i></button>
        </div>
        <div class="subbar-sep"></div>
        <div class="canvas-toolbar">
          <button class="filter-chip filter-chip--active"><i data-lucide="maximize-2"></i> Fit island · Blue</button>
          <button class="draw-tool-btn" title="Reset zoom (whole map)"><i data-lucide="scan"></i></button>
        </div>
        <span class="canvas-cursor">X -93 · Z -15</span>
        <div class="canvas-subbar-right"><span class="canvas-zoom">250%</span></div>
      </div>
      <p class="section-desc" style="margin-top:var(--space-2)">The author works one orbit unit at a time, so the
         toolbar offers a <strong>Fit island</strong> zoom and a <strong>reset-zoom</strong> back to the whole map.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>
